[This newswire shows a photo with the following explanatory text]:
Volunteers, equipped with what appeared to be disinfectant, man a
temporary checkpoint into a town, one of many roadblocks to stop
outsiders from entering the villages northwest of the Chinese capital
in Shanjiaying, China on Tue 24 May 2005. Chinese authorities
barred access on Tuesday to villages outside Beijing, where they
reportedly have slaughtered thousands of cows to stop an outbreak
of foot and mouth disease (FMD). Health and agriculture officials
have refused to confirm a report by Hong Kong's South China
Morning Post newspaper that cows have been slaughtered in an
attempt to stop an outbreak of FMD. [see the next item].
[Byline: AP Photo/Elizabeth Dalziel]
