ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[China sent to the OIE its 1st "Immediate notification report" on an
FMD outbreak in the eastern provinces of Shangdong and Jiangsu,
caused by FMDV serotype Asia 1, on 13 May 2005. If other
region(s) are indeed affected, they are not necessarily affected by
the same serotype; and, contrary to the statement in item 2 above
that Asia 1 serotype is "the most contagious" one, other serotypes --
particularly certain strains of the O serotype -- may be even more
infective and invasive, affecting several susceptible species.
The accumulating media-derived rumors about an FMD outbreak in
the vicinity of Beijing illuminate the need for a timely official
intervention, preferably in the form of an update to the OIE regarding
the FMD situation in the People's Republic of China. A weekly
update on outbreak evolution is prescribed in article 1.1.2.3. of
OIE's Terrestrial Animal Health Code. - Mod.AS]
